       <h5>#4. Baking Soda and Olive Oil as Home Remedy</h5>
       <p>Olive oil has been used since ancient days for skincare activities. Olive oil contains vitamins, minerals and fatty acids which help in the skin rejuvenation process.

        Baking soda is a powerful exfoliant which helps to remove the dead cells from the surface of the skin. Olive oil and baking soda together act as a great agent to remove wrinkles on the forehead.</p>
        <br>How to use</br>
        <img src="https://www.beinghappymom.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/word-image-41-1024x683.jpeg">

<br>Mix 1 teaspoon of olive oil with 1 teaspoon of baking soda</br>
<br>Gently rub the mixture on the forehead</br>
<br>Take a washcloth dipped in hot water and leave there on your forehead</br>
<br>After 5 minutes, wipe off the mixture using lukewarm water</br>
